Reference-contexts: 1 Introduction We are developing a trigger-system for the Fluorescence Detector proposed for the Pierre Auger Project. Our approach is based on the three-eyed detector with superman-layout and dual-mirrors as described by Paul Sommers <ref> [2] </ref>. The whole system has a modular structure and it is based on the mirror systems of every eye. We are implementing a configurable, hardware-based system in the mirrors, which allows a great variety of different parameters, for evaluating the first-level trigger.
